   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "f58e861b",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "# Part 1: Ollama"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "raw",
   "id": "dabb2340",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "What is Ollama?\n",
    "Ollama is a wrapper service around llama.cpp (and other inference engines).\n",
    "- A user-friendly API server\n",
    "- Model management system (pull, list, delete)\n",
    "- Built-in modelfile format for configuration\n",
    "- REST API that's OpenAI-compatible\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "Pros: Easy setup, great for beginners, model library\n",
    "Cons: Additional overhead, less control over inference parameters"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "c91842e6",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "# Part 2: Hardware Understanding"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "raw",
   "id": "59a0b9bb",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "\n",
    "- 10 CPU cores (6 performance + 4 efficiency)\n",
    "- 16GB+ unified memory (shared between CPU/GPU)\n",
    "- Metal GPU with 16-core neural engine\n",
    "Key Insight: On Apple Silicon, the GPU shares memory with the CPU (unified memory architecture). This means:\n",
    "- No data transfer overhead between CPU ↔ GPU\n",
    "- GPU can access all system RAM\n",
    "- Metal Performance Shaders (MPS) accelerate matrix operations\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "M1 Pro GPU Reality\n",
    "The M1 Pro has an integrated GPU with 16 cores built into the same chip as the CPU. It's not a separate graphics card like an NVIDIA RTX, but it IS a real GPU that can:\n",
    "- Run Metal shaders (Apple's GPU programming framework)\n",
    "- Accelerate matrix operations (critical for LLMs)\n",
    "- Process multiple sequences in parallel\n",
    "Key difference: It's unified memory architecture:\n",
    "- CPU and GPU share the same RAM\n",
    "- No copying data between CPU memory ↔ GPU memory\n",
    "- The GPU can access all 16GB+ of system RAM"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "f75bd936",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "# Part 3: Concurrency Problem"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "raw",
   "id": "d0dd4310",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "1. Memory-bound: Loading model into VRAM/RAM is expensive\n",
    "2. compute-intensive: Generating tokens uses CPU heavily \n",
    "3. Sequential in nature: Each token depends on previous tokens"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "47e2344b",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Concurrency Strategies"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "raw",
   "id": "4bee928b",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Strategy 1: Sequential Processing (naive)\n",
    "    \n",
    "Request 1 → Process → Response\n",
    "Request 2 → Process → Response\n",
    "Request 3 → Process → Response\n",
    "- Simple but slow for multiple users\n",
    "- Total time = sum of all request times"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "raw",
   "id": "7a9be165",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Strategy 2: True Parallelism\n",
    "\n",
    "Request 1 ↘\n",
    "Request 2 → [LLM Engine] → All responses simultaneously\n",
    "Request 3 ↗\n",
    "- Requires inference engine support\n",
    "- Limited by GPU memory and compute units\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "raw",
   "id": "5dc4fc31",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Strategy 3: Batching\n",
    "\n",
    "Batch 1: [Req1, Req2, Req3, Req4] → Process together\n",
    "Batch 2: [Req5, Req6, Req7, Req8] → Process together\n",
    "- Group requests together\n",
    "- Process multiple in one forward pass\n",
    "- More efficient GPU utilization"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "acdc573d",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "# Part 4: Understanding Parameters"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "raw",
   "id": "5d9ca23e",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "OLLAMA_NUM_PARALLEL=4      # How many concurrent requests\n",
    "OLLAMA_CONTEXT_LENGTH=2048 # Max tokens in context\n",
    "OLLAMA_MAX_LOADED_MODELS=1 # Models to keep in memory"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "raw",
   "id": "198ee667",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Ollama creates multiple \"slots\" in GPU  memory.  Each slot can handle one request. If you have 4 slots and 10 requests arrive: \n",
    "- 4 requests process immediately\n",
    "-  6 requests queue up \n",
    "-  As slots free up, queued requests start"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "29790cfb",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "# Part 5: Benchmarking Methodology"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "raw",
   "id": "24015ac4",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "1. Time to First Token (TTFT)\n",
    "- Time from request sent to first token received\n",
    "- Measures initialization overhead\n",
    "- Critical for user experience\n",
    "\n",
    "2. Total Generation Time\n",
    "- Time to complete entire response\n",
    "- Depends on output length\n",
    "\n",
    "3. Tokens Per Second (Throughput)\n",
    "- How fast tokens are generated\n",
    "- Higher = better\n",
    "\n",
    "4. Inter-Token Latency\n",
    "- Time between consecutive tokens\n",
    "- Measures streaming smoothness\n",
    "\n",
    "5. Concurrent Request Handling\n",
    "- How many simultaneous requests before degradation\n",
    "- Queue depth and wait times\n",
    "\n",
    "6. Memory Usage\n",
    "- Peak RAM/VRAM consumption\n",
    "- Memory efficiency"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "c7585429",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Scenarious to run"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "raw",
   "id": "13908e7c",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Scenario A: Single Request Baseline\n",
    "- 1 request, measure all metrics\n",
    "- Establish baseline performance\n",
    "\n",
    "Scenario B: Low Concurrency (5-10 requests)\n",
    "- 5 requests simultaneously\n",
    "- Tests basic parallelism\n",
    "\n",
    "Scenario C: Medium Concurrency (25-50 requests)\n",
    "- Stress test the system\n",
    "- Measures queue behavior\n",
    "\n",
    "Scenario D: Sustained Load\n",
    "- 1000 requests over time\n",
    "- Tests stability and memory leaks"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "30d1726c",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "# Part 6: Prompt Optimization Strategy"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "raw",
   "id": "ccfc2b67",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Why Prompt Size Matters\n",
    "Every token in your prompt:\n",
    "- Increases memory usage\n",
    "- Adds computation time\n",
    "- Slows down inference"
   ]
